# load(from:)

**Instance Method**

Loads the contents of the specified web history file.

## Declaration

```swift
func load(from URL: URL!) throws
```

## Parameters

- **URL**: The URL of the file to load. The file should have been created previously by a web history object. Note that the fileâ€™s format is private and should not be edited directly.

## Discussion

When successful, this method posts a notification ([doc://com.apple.webkit/documentation/WebKit/WebHistoryLoadedNotification]).



## Related Documentation

- **setOptionalShared(_:)**: Sets the web history object to share.
- **optionalShared()**: Returns a shared web history object, if one exists.

## Loading and Saving History Information

- **save(to:)**: Saves the web history to the specified file.
